            "text": "sales, takeout, and home delivery, either by affirmatively allowing this or by not enforcing existing prohibitions (9) (10) (11) . These measures may skirt open container laws and delivery permit requirements. Complete or partial bans on alcohol sales have been implemented during pandemic lockdowns in some places, including India, South Africa, Greenland, and Mexico yet this can increase demand for delivery (3, 12) . Post-pandemic, delivery businesses could constitute a new industry stakeholder pressuring governments to maintain newly relaxed policies.",
